# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Training | Scene: TrainingPathCaleb
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "She would ask Ephraim and Caleb to train her."
    new "She would ask Ephraim and Caleb to train her."

    old "They had shown kindness to her when she first came to the camp."
    new "They had shown kindness to her when she first came to the camp."

    old "Additionally, Sarah reasoned, two mentors would be better than one."
    new "Additionally, Sarah reasoned, two mentors would be better than one."

    old "Sarah had made her decision, and now she set out to put it into action."
    new "Sarah had made her decision, and now she set out to put it into action."

    old "She searched all over the camp, until eventually, she found both Caleb and Ephraim at the training ground, already practicing."
    new "She searched all over the camp, until eventually, she found both Caleb and Ephraim at the training ground, already practicing."

    old "Sarah observed the pair from a distance before she made her approach."
    new "Sarah observed the pair from a distance before she made her approach."

    old "They switched roles, each taking the attacking role and the defending role, before swapping."
    new "They switched roles, each taking the attacking role and the defending role, before swapping."

    old "One advanced, made a series of jabs and sweeps, and the other tried to parry."
    new "One advanced, made a series of jabs and sweeps, and the other tried to parry."

    old "They seemed very casual and joyful to Sarah. How she had been, she wondered, when all she knew was castle life."
    new "They seemed very casual and joyful to Sarah. How she had been, she wondered, when all she knew was castle life."

    old "She gathered up her courage and strode across the training grounds."
    new "She gathered up her courage and strode across the training grounds."

    old "Not yet noticed, she cleared her throat, getting both of their attention."
    new "Not yet noticed, she cleared her throat, getting both of their attention."

    old "Hey Sarah!"
    new "Hey Sarah!"

    old "Princess."
    new "Princess."

    old "Ephraim made a small bow."
    new "Ephraim made a small bow."

    old "Hey! Ooh, and Ephraim, please don't call me that. I'm really not anything special."
    new "Hey! Ooh, and Ephraim, please don't call me that. I'm really not anything special."

    old "Ephraim raised a hand."
    new "Ephraim raised a hand."

    old "Apologies, I thought it only proper. We both heard what has happened in Rosanna over the recent weeks...we hope you're carrying it well?"
    new "Apologies, I thought it only proper. We both heard what has happened in Rosanna over the recent weeks...we hope you're carrying it well?"

    old "Sarah felt a sting of pain."
    new "Sarah felt a sting of pain."

    old "She was out here, all alone, and here the world seemed to carry on as it always had."
    new "She was out here, all alone, and here the world seemed to carry on as it always had."

    old "Knowing that her countrymen suffered across the sea, that her nation was brought to ruin...it seemed unthinkable."
    new "Knowing that her countrymen suffered across the sea, that her nation was brought to ruin...it seemed unthinkable."

    old "Thank you for your consideration. It really means more than you can know."
    new "Thank you for your consideration. It really means more than you can know."

    old "Sarah didn't lie."
    new "Sarah didn't lie."

    old "No problem at all. But Sarah, it seemed like you were looking for us. Is there anything we can do for you?"
    new "No problem at all. But Sarah, it seemed like you were looking for us. Is there anything we can do for you?"

    old "Sarah wondered for a moment how she could phrase her request. In the end, she simply did."
    new "Sarah wondered for a moment how she could phrase her request. In the end, she simply did."

    old "I need your help."
    new "I need your help."

    old "I'm going to be taking the exam very soon, and I need a mentor to help me."
    new "I'm going to be taking the exam very soon, and I need a mentor to help me."

    old "I thought since you were both so nice to me when I first got here...maybe you could...help me?"
    new "I thought since you were both so nice to me when I first got here...maybe you could...help me?"

    old "Both Ephraim and Caleb looked somewhat surprised."
    new "Both Ephraim and Caleb looked somewhat surprised."

    old "Ooh...I didn't think you would wanna ask us. We're just normal soldiers, I figured you would have some fancy teacher or something."
    new "Ooh...I didn't think you would wanna ask us. We're just normal soldiers, I figured you would have some fancy teacher or something."

    old "I never got any formal training, and I don't have any money for a teacher...so...I hoped, since you were so nice to me, that you'd be willing to help me prepare for the exam."
    new "I never got any formal training, and I don't have any money for a teacher...so...I hoped, since you were so nice to me, that you'd be willing to help me prepare for the exam."

    old "Ephraim moved to answer, but Caleb was faster."
    new "Ephraim moved to answer, but Caleb was faster."

    old "He seemed genuinely excited."
    new "He seemed genuinely excited."

    old "Caleb immediatly began to gather training equipment and excercise gear, dropping it in a chaotic pile next to them."
    new "Caleb immediatly began to gather training equipment and excercise gear, dropping it in a chaotic pile next to them."

    old "Ephraim remained standing."
    new "Ephraim remained standing."

    old "We'll teach you, Sarah, but understand that the exam can be difficult. You'll have to commit yourself."
    new "We'll teach you, Sarah, but understand that the exam can be difficult. You'll have to commit yourself."

    old "I understand, and I will."
    new "I understand, and I will."

    old "With both men convinced, their training began right there."
    new "With both men convinced, their training began right there."

    old "Sarah's assumption soon proved correct. With both Ephraim and Caleb as her mentors, she found herself quickly learning the basics of fighting."
    new "Sarah's assumption soon proved correct. With both Ephraim and Caleb as her mentors, she found herself quickly learning the basics of fighting."

    old "Each time she sparred with one, the other would observe and give feedback."
    new "Each time she sparred with one, the other would observe and give feedback."

    old "In little time they had worked her to the bone. Sarah found herself drenched in sweat, her arms felt like lead."
    new "In little time they had worked her to the bone. Sarah found herself drenched in sweat, her arms felt like lead."

    old "I think that's enough."
    new "I think that's enough."

    old "Ephraim smiled as he walked over."
    new "Ephraim smiled as he walked over."

    old "Caleb joined them."
    new "Caleb joined them."

    old "Yeah, you did really good Sarah, especially for a first time."
    new "Yeah, you did really good Sarah, especially for a first time."

    old "Suddenly, Ephraim leaned into Caleb, and planted his lips on his."
    new "Suddenly, Ephraim leaned into Caleb, and planted his lips on his."

    old "The two shared a kiss, as if they had forgotten Sarah was there."
    new "The two shared a kiss, as if they had forgotten Sarah was there."

    old "In Rosanna, men didn't do these things with other men. It certainly wasn't allowed by the authorities, be it the state or the church."
    new "In Rosanna, men didn't do these things with other men. It certainly wasn't allowed by the authorities, be it the state or the church."

    old "To see these two men, not just do so, but openly and without any shame, it was something Sarah struggled to make sense of."
    new "To see these two men, not just do so, but openly and without any shame, it was something Sarah struggled to make sense of."

    old "A-a-are...y-you...a couple?"
    new "A-a-are...y-you...a couple?"

    old "Caleb and Ephraim broke their kiss."
    new "Caleb and Ephraim broke their kiss."

    old "Ooh, I forgot, where you're from this isn't allowed right?"
    new "Ooh, I forgot, where you're from this isn't allowed right?"

    old "It's different, in here. Vaelen doesn't care, and really, most places on this side of the ocean don't really care."
    new "It's different, in here. Vaelen doesn't care, and really, most places on this side of the ocean don't really care."

    old "We've just been on the road together for a long time...and as soldiers...you know...men have urges..."
    new "We've just been on the road together for a long time...and as soldiers...you know...men have urges..."

    old "Ephraim added."
    new "Ephraim added."

    old "And there aren't always women around."
    new "And there aren't always women around."

    old "So you're both..."
    new "So you're both..."

    old "Caleb shook his head."
    new "Caleb shook his head."

    old "I really don't mind either which way, but Ephraim mostly goes for guys."
    new "I really don't mind either which way, but Ephraim mostly goes for guys."

    old "So it works out."
    new "So it works out."

    old "Caleb laughed."
    new "Caleb laughed."

    old "Sarah tried to process all this information. She had never really considered that perhaps the rigid rules of her society, only really applied to that society."
    new "Sarah tried to process all this information. She had never really considered that perhaps the rigid rules of her society, only really applied to that society."

    old "That people could live so freely...and confusingly...it was a lot for her to make sense of."
    new "That people could live so freely...and confusingly...it was a lot for her to make sense of."

    old "But in the end, they seemed happy, and Sarah wondered how anyone could really object to that."
    new "But in the end, they seemed happy, and Sarah wondered how anyone could really object to that."

    old "Well, uhm, where I'm from might be different, but I don't mind."
    new "Well, uhm, where I'm from might be different, but I don't mind."

    old "Sarah smiled at them and found them smiling back."
    new "Sarah smiled at them and found them smiling back."

    old "Walking back to the tent, the three found themselves lost in deep conversation."
    new "Walking back to the tent, the three found themselves lost in deep conversation."

